Feedback:
There is clear evidence of a problem consistent with 'SwitchInternalFault'. When the switch was in the closed position, continuity testing revealed an open circuit (extremely high resistance: 1,000,000,000 Ω measured versus 0.01 Ω nominal). This indicates the switch is not establishing proper internal contact when closed, which is anomalous behavior. When the switch was opened, as expected, the circuit remained open—this portion of the test is nominal, but since there was no continuity in the closed state, the switch is internally faulty. Recommend replacing or repairing the switch.
